                    question: "Prove by the mathematical induction that $4+8+12+\\ldots+4 n=2 n(n+1)$ for all natural numbers $n$. <br> <strong>Solution</strong><br>Let $P(n)$ denote the statement $4+8+12+\\ldots+4 n=2 n(n+1)$ for all natural numbers $n$. <br>For $n=1$, <br>L.H.S =4, <br>R.H.S =2(1)(1+1)=4 <br>L.H.S = R.H.S <br>P(1) is true. <br>Assume that <br>A. P(k+1) is true <br>B. P(k-1) is true <br>C. P(2) is true <br>D. P(k) is true <br><strong>Answer:</strong> {1:dropdown:A,B,C,D:D}<br><br>i.e., $4+8+12+\\ldots+4 k=2 k(k+1)$ <br>We will show that P(k+1) is true. <br><br>For n =k+1, <br>L.H.S = <br>A. L.H.S =2 k(k+1)+4 <br>B. L.H.S =2 k(k+1)+1 <br>C. L.H.S =2 k(k+1)+4(k+1) <br>D. L.H.S =3 k+5 <br><strong>Answer:</strong> {2:dropdown:A,B,C,D:C}<br><br>R.H.S = <br>A. R.H.S =2(k+1)(k+2) <br>B. R.H.S =(2 k+1)(k+2) <br>C. R.H.S =2(k+1)(k+1) <br>D. R.H.S =(k+2)(k+1) <br><strong>Answer:</strong> {3:dropdown:A,B,C,D:A}<br><br>L.H.S = R.H.S <br>P(k+1) is true. <br>Hence, by the principle of Mathematical induction, the statement P( n ) is true for all natural numbers n.",
